      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Sinclair Lewis (1885-1951) was an American novelist, short-story writer, and playwright. He was the first American to be 
	  awarded the Nobel Prize in Literature, in 1930.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Sinclair Lewis Collection</emph> consists of correspondence.  All letters are photopies, no originals.  The finding aid originally listed a photograph and a part of a manuscript; these items could not be located during rehousing (2018).</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Chronologically.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
